{
  "texts": [
    "Our insights and observations pave the way for future research and development.",
    "We hope that our efforts will inspire the community to advance this work, guided by our future directions.",
    "Discussions on Stratified Masking rates We assigned masking rates of 0.15 to stopwords, 0.20 to Dale-Chall easy words, and 0.25 to other words, focusing on more informative and kid-specific vocabulary.",
    "This approach led to a masking ratio of stopwords: Dale-Chall words: other words = 0.15:0.20:0.25, increasing in increments of 0.05.",
    "We recognize that alternative ratios, such as 0.15:0.25:0.35 with increments of 0.10, are also feasible."
  ]
}